<ns6508:section xmlns:ns6508="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="resources.information.technologies.java.j2se.exceptionHandling.uncaughtExceptionHandlers.introduction.introduction">  
  <ns6509:title xmlns:ns6509="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Introduction</ns6509:title>
  <ns6510:para xmlns:ns6510="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    Exceptions not called within the calling hierarchy of a thread eneded up being caught by
    <ns6511:literal xmlns:ns6511="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">ThreadGroup</ns6511:literal> which, by default, printed the thread's name, exception name,
    exception message and stack trace.
  </ns6510:para>
  <ns6512:para xmlns:ns6512="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    Using <ns6513:literal xmlns:ns6513="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">UncaughtExceptionHandler</ns6513:literal>'s one can specify either application wide or
    on a per thread basis how uncaught exceptions should be handled.
  </ns6512:para>
</ns6508:section>